items.title: Phillips out of lineup with lower back tightness
items.summary: Angels second baseman Brandon Phillips sat out Saturday's game against the Rangers with lower back tightness, though manager Mike Scioscia said he is day to day and could return to action on Sunday.
items.content: Angels second baseman Brandon Phillips sat out Saturday's game against the Rangers with lower back tightness, though manager Mike Scioscia said he is day to day and could return to action on Sunday.

items.title: Lindor's extra-base hit streak sets club mark
items.summary: Francisco Lindor is playing the best baseball of his life, and it's coming at just the right time. He logged three hits, including a clutch two-run double, in Saturday's 8-4 win over the Royals.

items.title: Mazara out of lineup with left quad tightness
items.summary: Rangers outfielder Nomar Mazara was out of the lineup on Saturday night against the Angels with tightness in his left quad muscle. He was not happy about it.

items.title: Hays' 1st hit, HR give O's reason to smile
items.summary: As the Orioles' postseason hopes dwindle, the team's young prospects have given them something to feel good about amid a tough weekend series in the Bronx.
